INSERT INTO `releases` VALUES (1,'August Burns Red','Found In Far Away Places','1.jpg','ABR123876','2014-06-18','On 2013&#39;s excellent Rescue &amp; Restore, August Burns Red further expanded their definition of metalcore by making the notoriously atonal and punishing genre a little more hummable, albeit at a speed that would require Herculean murmuring skills. Found in Far Away Places, the band&#39;s seventh studio long player, doubles down on the group&#39;s more progressive leanings, offering up a diverse (for metalcore) 11-track set that evokes a wide range of influences, from Killswitch Engage to Ennio Morricone and Iron Maiden. As per usual, the band&#39;s breakdowns are huge, technically impressive heat blasts that fulfill any and all obligations to the genre, but they&#39;re tempered by equally dramatic instances of elliptical, palm-muted riffing as steeped in power metal as they are post-hardcore. This penchant for pairing the soaring with the sordid is best exemplified on early stand-out cuts like &quot;The Wake,&quot; &quot;Martyr,&quot; and &quot;Separating the Seas,&quot; the latter of which pairs a tumultuous front and back half with a chamber folk center driven by flamenco-inspired guitar and pizzicato violin. Elsewhere, the band flirts with the mainstream on the soaring &quot;Identity,&quot; the emotionally charged &quot;Majoring in the Mirrors&quot; descends into a dark, hill folk hoedown, and the anthemic closer, &quot;Vanguard,&quot; manages to blend the beefy, hook-filled stoner rock of Torche with the kinetic, electro-paranoia of Muse. That the band never lose themselves in the process of these myriad digressions is impressive to say the least, but what&#39;s most notable about Found in Far Away Places is how fluid the ride is. Most metalcore outfits just dig in, plant a flag, and defend the perimeter; August Burns Red is already on to the next village.','<ul>\r\n	<li>The Wake</li>\r\n	<li>Martyr</li>\r\n	<li>Identity</li>\r\n	<li>Separating the Seas</li>\r\n	<li>Ghosts (featuring&nbsp;Jeremy McKinnon)</li>\r\n	<li>Majoring in the Minors</li>\r\n	<li>Everlasting Ending (featuring&nbsp;Paul Waggoner)</li>\r\n	<li>Broken Promises</li>\r\n	<li>Blackwood</li>\r\n	<li>Twenty-One Grams</li>\r\n	<li>Vanguard</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/found-in-far-away-places/id981106718','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Burns_Red_Found_In_Far_Away_Places_Instrume?id=Brmfpdjainmjqxugbpklmwycwx4','https://play.spotify.com/album/7xkmcz0mRIJeXrKKtsxhB7','http://www.deezer.com/album/10703612','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"5\";i:1;s:1:\"7\";i:2;s:2:\"12\";}',11),(2,'Breakdown Of Sanity','Perception','2.jpg','BOS32421','2013-10-18','Третій студійний альбом &laquo;Perception&raquo; був виданий 18 жовтня 2013 року. Крім того відбувся тур з такими гуртами, як&nbsp;August Burns Red&nbsp;та&nbsp;Architects&nbsp;Geplant. Ці концерти відбулися в контексті з&nbsp;Impericon Progression Tour&nbsp;протягом місяця квітня. Концертний тур повинен був містити п&#39;ять концертів разом з&nbsp;Herford,&nbsp;Bochum,&nbsp;Stuttgart,&nbsp;W&uuml;rzburg&nbsp;та&nbsp;M&uuml;nchen. Разом з Architects, August Burns Red та Breakdown of Sanity були також добре відомі&nbsp;Callejon, а також&nbsp;Adept. Грав гурт&nbsp;Progression Tour, який також був на&nbsp;Impericon Festival&nbsp;в&nbsp;Лейпцигу&nbsp;та&nbsp;Wien.<br />\r\nСвій перший концерт в 2013 році гурт грав 11 січня в Цюриху разом з&nbsp;Scream Your Name&nbsp;в Берні. 3 червня 2013 року було оголошено, що Breakdown of Sanity вперше грає на&nbsp;With Full Force.&nbsp;Група грала по суботах в &laquo;Hard Bowl Stage&raquo;.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Exordium</li>\r\n	<li>Crumble</li>\r\n	<li>Hero</li>\r\n	<li>The Writer</li>\r\n	<li>Blind</li>\r\n	<li>Scissorhands</li>\r\n	<li>Perception</li>\r\n	<li>The Gift</li>\r\n	<li>Deliverance</li>\r\n	<li>Chapters</li>\r\n	<li>Broken Wings</li>\r\n	<li>Invisible Scars</li>\r\n	<li>Cardiac Silhouette</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/perception/id715259531','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Breakdown_of_Sanity_Perception?id=Bkyyx7uokmqhs6hscnxqhws4bui','https://play.spotify.com/album/6zc9Wh5qCagfHMNEj8AueP','http://www.deezer.com/album/6981816','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"1\";i:1;s:1:\"2\";i:2;s:1:\"7\";}',9),(3,'Memphis May Fire','This Light I Hold','3.jpg','MMF23462','2016-10-28','This Light I Hold&nbsp;is the fifth studio album by&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;Memphis May Fire. It was released on the October 28, 2016 by&nbsp;Rise Records.<br />\r\nThe band premiered the first single &quot;Carry On&quot; on&nbsp;BBC Radio 1&nbsp;on August 28, 2016. On September 23, 2016, Memphis May Fire released the title track and second single to their new album, &quot;This Light I Hold,&quot; which features&nbsp;Jacoby Shaddix&nbsp;(of&nbsp;Papa Roach), accompanied with a music video.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Out of It</li>\r\n	<li>Carry On</li>\r\n	<li>Wanting More</li>\r\n	<li>Sever the Ties</li>\r\n	<li>The Enemy</li>\r\n	<li>This Light I Hold (featuring Jacoby Shaddix)</li>\r\n	<li>That&#39;s Just Life</li>\r\n	<li>Letting Go</li>\r\n	<li>The Antidote</li>\r\n	<li>Better Things</li>\r\n	<li>Not Over Yet (featuring Larry Soliman)</li>\r\n	<li>Unashamed</li>\r\n	<li>Live It Well</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/this-light-i-hold/id1145610247','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Memphis_May_Fire_This_Light_I_Hold?id=Bfzdxnzidw57vzdpm56p66ahf5y','https://play.spotify.com/album/1JHoc7xehkMbpENGv4pbIt','http://www.deezer.com/album/14400878','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"2\";i:1;s:2:\"10\";i:2;s:2:\"11\";}',16),(4,'Animals as Leaders','Animals as Leaders','4.jpg','AAS67829','2009-04-28','Animals as Leaders&nbsp;is the debut album by&nbsp;progressive metal&nbsp;group&nbsp;Animals as Leaders. It was released on April 28, 2009 by&nbsp;Prosthetic Records. In 2015, a reissue titled&nbsp;Animals as Leaders &ndash; Encore Edition&nbsp;was released with bonus tracks.<br />\r\nBefore&nbsp;Animals as Leaders&nbsp;Tosin Abasi&nbsp;was a member of&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band Reflux that had been disbanded. Reflux&#39;s former record label&nbsp;Prosthetic Records&nbsp;saw Abasi&#39;s guitar work and asked him to create a solo album for them. Abasi initially declined, feeling such an endeavor would be &quot;egotistical and unnecessary&quot;. Afterwards, Abasi enrolled in the Atlanta Institute of Music which helped give him new creative ideas for music composition. Abasi later changed his mind saying that &quot;doing a solo album seemed to make a lot more sense&quot;, and decided to take the label&#39;s offer. However, he did not want the project&#39;s new album to just represent the idea of one person. Abasi&#39;s school experience aided him in developing ideas for the album. While at school he learned fundamental harmony, jazz playing standards, and improved on playing classical guitar.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Tempting Time</li>\r\n	<li>Soraya</li>\r\n	<li>Thoroughly at Home</li>\r\n	<li>On Impulse</li>\r\n	<li>Tessitura</li>\r\n	<li>Behaving Badly</li>\r\n	<li>The Price of Everything and the Value of Nothing</li>\r\n	<li>CAFO</li>\r\n	<li>Inamorata</li>\r\n	<li>Point to Point</li>\r\n	<li>Modern Meat</li>\r\n	<li>Song of Solomon</li>\r\n	<li>Wave of Babies</li>\r\n	<li>Kalimba</li>\r\n	<li>Orea (Demo)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/animals-as-leaders/id965454467','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Animals_As_Leaders_Animals_as_Leaders_Encore_Editi?id=Bgokr5x7iprjxypvobkrz5xrsia','https://play.spotify.com/album/5hVRBZCUCcU3UIhxNikyhf','http://www.deezer.com/album/10715136','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"3\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:2:\"12\";}',3),(5,'August Burns Red','Constellations','5.jpg','ABR29842','2009-07-14','Constellations&nbsp;is the third studio album by&nbsp;August Burns Red.&nbsp;The album was released on July 14, 2009 through&nbsp;Solid State Records.<br />\r\nOn the band&#39;s MySpace page, they released four singles from the album, &quot;Thirty and Seven&quot; and &quot;Existence,&quot; with &quot;Thirty and Seven&quot; available for download on the&nbsp;iTunes Store.[citation needed]&nbsp;&quot;Ocean of Apathy&quot;, the third track from the then-upcoming album, was released on Monday June 29, 2009.[citation needed]&nbsp;&quot;Meddler&quot; was released on July 6, 2009 and was shown on the band&#39;s Myspace.[citation needed]&nbsp;On July 7, 2009, the band posted the entire album on their Myspace page.[citation needed]&nbsp;They then would sell the album days ahead of the release at the beginning of their tour with&nbsp;Enter Shikari,&nbsp;Iwrestledabearonce&nbsp;and&nbsp;Blessthefall, starting with the&nbsp;Recher Theatre&nbsp;in Towson, Maryland on July 10, 2009.','Thirty and Seven<br />\r\nExistence<br />\r\nOcean of Apathy<br />\r\nWhite Washed<br />\r\nMarianas Trench<br />\r\nThe Escape Artist<br />\r\nIndonesia&quot; (feat. Tommy Giles Rogers)<br />\r\nParadox<br />\r\nMeridian<br />\r\nRationalist<br />\r\nMeddler<br />\r\nCrusades','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/constellations/id651632111','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Burns_Red_Constellations?id=Bcpymmi5f3x6kq2epufvviajudq','https://play.spotify.com/album/31zSMOMuHGKptag35siG2e','http://www.deezer.com/album/6594166','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"1\";i:1;s:1:\"3\";i:2;s:1:\"7\";}',4),(6,'Trivium','In Waves','6.jpg','TR235423','2011-08-02','In Waves&nbsp;&mdash; пятый студийный альбом&nbsp;американской&nbsp;металкор-группы&nbsp;Trivium, выпущенный 2 августа 2011 лейблом&nbsp;Roadrunner Records[19]. За первую неделю было продано 22,000 копий пластинки, благодаря чему альбом занял тринадцатую позицию в&nbsp;Billboard&nbsp;200&nbsp;и первую в&nbsp;Billboard&nbsp;Hard Rock charts[20].<br />\r\nПо звучанию альбом ближе к&nbsp;Ascendancy, чем к&nbsp;The Crusade&nbsp;и&nbsp;Shogun, так как в нём преобладает мелодик-металкор[1][2][3][4].<br />\r\nIn Waves&nbsp;&mdash; это первый альбом группы с новым барабанщиком Ником Августо, заменившим ушедшего в 2009 году Трэвиса Смита.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Capsizing The Sea</li>\r\n	<li>In Waves</li>\r\n	<li>Inception Of The End</li>\r\n	<li>Dusk Dismantled</li>\r\n	<li>Watch The World Burn</li>\r\n	<li>Black</li>\r\n	<li>A Skyline&#39;s Severance</li>\r\n	<li>Built To Fall</li>\r\n	<li>Caustic Are The Ties That Bind</li>\r\n	<li>Forsake Not The Dream</li>\r\n	<li>Drowning In Slow Motion[Special Edition Track]</li>\r\n	<li>A Grey So Dark[Special Edition Track]</li>\r\n	<li>Chaos Reigns</li>\r\n	<li>Of All These Yesterdays</li>\r\n	<li>Leaving This World Behind</li>\r\n	<li>Shattering The Skies Above</li>\r\n	<li>Slave New World</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/in-waves-special-edition/id446308612','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Trivium_In_Waves?id=Bx7yxlvcklqa2mxsmm5os5gq6tq','https://play.spotify.com/album/38sCkVGoLKjqFcOrTKTEC4','http://www.deezer.com/album/1202353','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"5\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:2:\"10\";}',6),(7,'Texas in July ','Bloodwork','7.jpg','TIJ9523','2014-09-16','Bloodwork&nbsp;is the fourth and final&nbsp;studio album by American&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;Texas in July. The album was released on September 16, 2014, through&nbsp;Equal Vision Records, and is the band&#39;s only album with vocalist JT Cavey.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Broken Soul</li>\r\n	<li>Sweetest Poison</li>\r\n	<li>Pseudo Self</li>\r\n	<li>Defenseless</li>\r\n	<li>The Void (feat. Levi Benton)</li>\r\n	<li>Inner Demons</li>\r\n	<li>Decamilli (feat. Zack Hansen)</li>\r\n	<li>Nooses</li>\r\n	<li>The Tightrope</li>\r\n	<li>Illuminate</li>\r\n	<li>Bloodwork</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/bloodwork/id911034869','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Texas_In_July_Bloodwork?id=Bvlt4cef4mse2j563mabg2aam2u','https://play.spotify.com/album/1Q2VgHA0xaIIU87ZeSOUPW','http://www.deezer.com/album/8436390','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"2\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:2:\"12\";}',13),(8,'I, The Breather','Truth and Purpose','8.jpg','ITB324236','2012-02-27','Truth and Purpose&nbsp;is the second album by band&nbsp;I, The Breather. The album was released on February 28, 2012 through&nbsp;Sumerian Records. The video for the song&nbsp;False Profit&nbsp;was released on May 4, 2012','<ul>\r\n	<li>False Profit</li>\r\n	<li>The Beginning</li>\r\n	<li>Bruised &amp; Broken</li>\r\n	<li>Mentalist (feat. Micah Kinard)</li>\r\n	<li>Meaning</li>\r\n	<li>Lunar</li>\r\n	<li>Knights &amp; Pawns</li>\r\n	<li>Judgement</li>\r\n	<li>Rephaim</li>\r\n	<li>4.12.11</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/truth-and-purpose/id611043776','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/I_The_Breather_Truth_And_Purpose?id=Bdyobqfl7h6y7mxt3pgldhw3wq4','https://play.spotify.com/album/5ZHSPoU7dVluS6YEPOFrTk','http://www.deezer.com/album/6545902','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"2\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:1:\"7\";}',7),(9,'Bury Tomorrow','The Union of Crowns','9.jpg','BT124892','2012-06-13','The Union of Crowns&nbsp;is the second studio album from British&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;Bury Tomorrow. The album was released on 13 July 2012 on&nbsp;Nuclear Blast. It recorded within the first few months of 2012. The album released was delayed several time by the band in attempt to find a record label who could provide international distribution simultaneously.<br />\r\nThe album received mixed to positive reception from critics. With critics primarily praising the album song writing and sonic improvement from the band&#39;s predecessor,&nbsp;Portraits, negative criticism stemmed from its lack of innovation and the album&#39;s sometimes considered excessive length.<br />\r\n&nbsp;','<ul>\r\n	<li>Redeemer</li>\r\n	<li>The Maiden</li>\r\n	<li>Lionheart</li>\r\n	<li>Message to a King</li>\r\n	<li>An Honourable Reign</li>\r\n	<li>Knight Life</li>\r\n	<li>Royal Blood</li>\r\n	<li>Bitemarks</li>\r\n	<li>Abdication of Power</li>\r\n	<li>Kingdom</li>\r\n	<li>1603</li>\r\n	<li>Sceptres</li>\r\n	<li>Vacant Throne</li>\r\n	<li>A Curse</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-union-of-crowns/id538246277','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Bury_Tomorrow_The_Union_Of_Crowns?id=Brfaj2vq6dbuvyeka4v5yd2le24','https://play.spotify.com/album/3Pvm3GkHN5iQP5jfRvpEdi','http://www.deezer.com/album/3666631','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"3\";i:1;s:1:\"8\";i:2;s:2:\"11\";}',8),(10,'Bullet For My Valentine','Scream Aim Fire','10.jpg','BFMV12403','2008-01-27','Scream Aim Fire&nbsp;- студійний альбом&nbsp;уельської&nbsp;групи&nbsp;Bullet For My Valentine, який був випущений 28 січня 2008 року.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Scream Aim Fire</li>\r\n	<li>Eye Of The Storm</li>\r\n	<li>Hearts Burst Into Fire</li>\r\n	<li>Waking The Demon</li>\r\n	<li>Disappear</li>\r\n	<li>Deliver Us From Evil</li>\r\n	<li>Take It Out On Me</li>\r\n	<li>Say Goodnight</li>\r\n	<li>End Of Days</li>\r\n	<li>Last To Know</li>\r\n	<li>Forever And Always</li>\r\n	<li>No Easy Way Out</li>\r\n	<li>Ashes Of The Innocent</li>\r\n	<li>Creeping Death</li>\r\n	<li>Road To Nowhere</li>\r\n	<li>Watching Us Die Tonight</li>\r\n	<li>One Good Reason Why</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/scream-aim-fire/id272198989','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Bullet_For_My_Valentine_Scream_Aim_Fire?id=Bjaxwbvfyc5zfwj4xkc65fncmfa','https://play.spotify.com/album/4rmEmbA5eugmKqzn9mHPdp','http://www.deezer.com/album/71698','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"5\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:1:\"9\";}',2),(11,'Blessthefall','To Those Left Behind','11.jpg','BTF123421','2015-08-09','To Those Left Behind&nbsp;(с&nbsp;англ. &mdash;&thinsp;&laquo;Тем, кто остался позади&raquo;)&nbsp;&mdash; пятый студийный альбом&nbsp;металкор-группы&nbsp;Blessthefall, изданный 18 сентября 2015 года на лейбле&nbsp;Fearless Records. С альбома вышло два сингла: первый, &laquo;Up in Flames&raquo;, был выпущен во время участия группы в&nbsp;Vans Warped Tour 2015, 9 июля 2015; второй, &laquo;Walk on Water&raquo;&nbsp;&mdash; 9 августа 2015.<br />\r\nВ апреле 2015 года группа сообщила о начале работы над пятым альбомом в студии с Джоуи Стерджисом (англ.&nbsp;Joey Sturgis)[3]. В июне, в течение Warped Tour 2015, они объявили, что альбом выйдет 18 сентября на лейбле&nbsp;Fearless Records. Описывая альбом, фронтмен группы&nbsp;Боу Бокан&nbsp;сказал: &laquo;своей группой мы постоянно пытаемся переплюнуть самих себя, подниматься ступенькой выше каждой записью. Этим новым альбомом мы сделали огромный чёртов прыжок вперёд и находимся на пике, как музыканты и как авторы песен. Мы с нетерпением предвкушаем, куда приведёт нас наш альбом&raquo;[4]. Было обявлено, что купившие альбом через сайт Merchnow получат бонус-трек: акустическую версию песни &laquo;Condition//Comatose&raquo;','<ul>\r\n	<li>Decayer</li>\r\n	<li>Walk On Water</li>\r\n	<li>Dead Air</li>\r\n	<li>Up In Flames</li>\r\n	<li>Against The Waves</li>\r\n	<li>Looking Down From The Edge</li>\r\n	<li>Keep What We Love &amp; Burn The Rest</li>\r\n	<li>Condition // Comatose</li>\r\n	<li>Oathbreaker</li>\r\n	<li>To Those Left Behind</li>\r\n	<li>Departures</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/to-those-left-behind/id1022945879','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Blessthefall_To_Those_Left_Behind?id=Ba7n7tx6ylty5ymk5bflaz2cm7u','https://play.spotify.com/album/3g2RmbWlMS55PcdN2AdcWI','http://www.deezer.com/album/11225492','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"1\";i:1;s:1:\"3\";i:2;s:2:\"10\";}',14),(12,'August Burns Red','Messengers','12.jpg','ABR32452','2007-06-19','Messengers&nbsp;is the second album released by&nbsp;melodic metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;August Burns Red&nbsp;through&nbsp;Solid State Records,[4]&nbsp;and their first with vocalist&nbsp;Jake Luhrs&nbsp;and bass player Dustin Davidson. It sold 9,000 copies in its first week on sale, and went on to sell over 80,000. A video for the song &quot;Composure&quot; was recorded and was released as a single on September 6, 2007. The second video from this album, for the song &quot;Back Burner&quot;, premiered on Myspace Music on August 13, 2008. A vinyl copy of this record was also released with limited press numbers through the band&#39;s former label,&nbsp;CI Records.','<ul>\r\n	<li>The Truth Of A Liar</li>\r\n	<li>Up Against The Ropes</li>\r\n	<li>Back Burner</li>\r\n	<li>The Blinding Light</li>\r\n	<li>Composure</li>\r\n	<li>Vital Signs</li>\r\n	<li>The Eleventh Hour</li>\r\n	<li>The Balance</li>\r\n	<li>Black Sheep</li>\r\n	<li>An American Dream</li>\r\n	<li>Redemption</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/messengers/id651627539','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Burns_Red_Messengers?id=Bhl6ysx2psikzfsiaogfrk3n5nq','https://play.spotify.com/album/5IMDg8tXz2hZKflfPazVzO','http://www.deezer.com/album/692937','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"1\";i:1;s:1:\"5\";i:2;s:1:\"7\";}',1),(13,'Intervals','The Shape of Colour','13.jpg','I213456','2015-12-04','On June 23, 2015, Lukas and Anup announced on Facebook that they are no longer a part of Intervals. This separation was caused by different expectations about the direction of Intervals (instrumental music or not). Aaron is currently the only member of the band, but the next album will feature Cameron McLellan (Protest The Hero) on bass guitar, and Travis Orbin (Darkest Hour, Periphery, Sky Eats Airplane) on drums.[2]&nbsp;The album entitled&nbsp;The Shape of Colour&nbsp;was released in December 4, 2015.','<ul>\r\n	<li>I&#39;m Awake</li>\r\n	<li>Sure Shot</li>\r\n	<li>Fable</li>\r\n	<li>Sweet Tooth</li>\r\n	<li>Black Box</li>\r\n	<li>Slight of Hand</li>\r\n	<li>Meridian</li>\r\n	<li>Libra</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-shape-of-colour/id1048222984','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Intervals_The_Shape_of_Colour?id=Bikm3clkpirubo7f7t7gyxabyfq','https://play.spotify.com/album/4MYLm8Uxayy4UyqFHPHfBB','http://www.deezer.com/album/11398376','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"3\";i:1;s:1:\"4\";i:2;s:1:\"8\";}',15),(14,'Within the Ruins','Phenomena','14.jpg','WTR23480','2014-07-22','Blending the mechanical with the visceral, Within the Ruins create a terrifying juggernaut of an album on their fourth effort, Phenomena. Executing their relentless deathcore with almost robotic precision, the band create a sound that feels like an unstoppable, uncaring machine whose only goal is to grind the listener into a fine paste. Helping to paint this picture is Phenomena&#39;s heavily processed production, giving every element of Within the Ruins&#39; sound a sense of sterile perfection, as if the band were performing surgery on their songs rather than playing them. While this might normally leave an album feeling lifeless, the band&#39;s impressive musicianship and driving songwriting provide the album with just enough humanity to keep listeners engaged long enough to experience the album&#39;s stark brutality.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Gods Amongst Men</li>\r\n	<li>The Other</li>\r\n	<li>Calling Card</li>\r\n	<li>Hegira</li>\r\n	<li>Ronin</li>\r\n	<li>Enigma</li>\r\n	<li>Clockwork</li>\r\n	<li>Eternal Shore</li>\r\n	<li>Dark Monarch</li>\r\n	<li>Sentinel</li>\r\n	<li>Ataxia III</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ru/album/phenomena/id886821030','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Within_The_Ruins_Phenomena?id=Bbeiikjk2gohewzzrjy25ldp22e','https://play.spotify.com/album/0zT0ra3BjEICTOfq4myxGO','http://www.deezer.com/album/8148986','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"8\";i:1;s:2:\"12\";i:2;s:2:\"13\";}',12),(15,'August Burns Red','Home','15.jpg','ABR86332','2010-09-28','Home&nbsp;is a&nbsp;live album&nbsp;by&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;August Burns Red&nbsp;released through&nbsp;Solid State Records in a CD/DVD format. It was filmed live on June 4, 2010 at Warehouse 54 in&nbsp;Manheim, Pennsylvania&nbsp;and was released on September 28, 2010 through&nbsp;Solid State Records.<br />\r\nAugust Burns Red played different songs from their previous albums. The performance featured many fan favorites from the band&rsquo;s three full-length albums,&nbsp;Constellations, 2007&rsquo;s&nbsp;Messengers&nbsp;and 2005&rsquo;s&nbsp;Thrill Seeker.<br />\r\nThe show drew a sold-out crowd of 1250 people who wanted to participate in the performance, including some who traveled internationally, from as close as Montreal to as far as away as Amsterdam.[8]&nbsp;Home&nbsp;also features a bonus video documentary called &quot;Away Games&quot; and featured August Burns Red being interviewed on how they were formed and what they had experienced. It also featured some footage of them touring and fans being interviewed on how August Burns Red had influenced their lives.','<ul>\r\n	<li>Intro</li>\r\n	<li>Back Burner</li>\r\n	<li>Whitewashed</li>\r\n	<li>Your Little Suburbia Is in Ruins</li>\r\n	<li>The Eleventh Hour</li>\r\n	<li>Meddler</li>\r\n	<li>Truth of a Liar</li>\r\n	<li>Mariana&#39;s Trench</li>\r\n	<li>Thirty and Seven</li>\r\n	<li>Existence</li>\r\n	<li>Meridian</li>\r\n	<li>Shot Below the Belt</li>\r\n	<li>Up Against the Ropes</li>\r\n	<li>Composure</li>\r\n	<li>The Seventh Trumpet</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/home/id651679469','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Burns_Red_Home?id=Bdqgaxztzdr3edkveymi5homxcu','https://play.spotify.com/album/44QBeZW1UvdA6dekIXWP3s','http://www.deezer.com/album/6594168','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"1\";i:1;s:1:\"5\";i:2;s:2:\"12\";}',5),(16,'Memphis May Fire','Unconditional','16.jpg','MMF239347','2014-03-25','Unconditional&nbsp;is the fourth album by&nbsp;metalcore&nbsp;band&nbsp;Memphis May Fire. It was released on the March 25, 2014 by&nbsp;Rise Records&nbsp;and distributed by&nbsp;Fontana Distribution. The deluxe edition was released on July 17, 2015.&nbsp;Unconditional&nbsp;debuted at No. 4 on the&nbsp;Billboard&nbsp;200,[18]&nbsp;No. 1 on the Top Rock Albums and the&nbsp;Billboard&nbsp;Alternative Albums&nbsp;chart,[19][20]&nbsp;selling around 27,000 copies in the first week. The album has sold 83,000 copies in the United States as of September 2016.&nbsp;On February 6, 2014 the first single, &quot;No Ordinary Love&quot; was streamed through the Rise Records YouTube channel, and the official track listing was also released on this date.[12]&nbsp;The band later released &quot;Sleepless Nights&quot; on February 24[13]&nbsp;and then &quot;Beneath The Skin&quot; on March 11, 2014.[14][15]&nbsp;On March 13, 2014, Rise Records released a playlist of the full album on YouTube,[16]&nbsp;announced by Mullins who tweeted, &quot;Sometimes you gotta leak your own record!&quot;','<ul>\r\n	<li>No Ordinary Love</li>\r\n	<li>Beneath the Skin</li>\r\n	<li>Sleepless Nights</li>\r\n	<li>The Answer</li>\r\n	<li>Possibilities</li>\r\n	<li>Speechless</li>\r\n	<li>The Rose</li>\r\n	<li>Not Enough</li>\r\n	<li>Need To Be</li>\r\n	<li>Pharisees</li>\r\n	<li>Divinity</li>\r\n	<li>My Generation</li>\r\n	<li>Stay the Course</li>\r\n	<li>Beneath the Skin (Acoustic)</li>\r\n	<li>Need To Be (Acoustic)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/unconditional-deluxe-edition/id1022062224','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Memphis_May_Fire_Unconditional_Deluxe_Edition?id=B4jxhqdyrlf2vububsgzmdma5ya','https://play.spotify.com/album/69MPKTXSaWG4H1zk4Z8qN0','http://www.deezer.com/album/10885752','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"3\";i:1;s:1:\"9\";i:2;s:2:\"11\";}',10),(17,'Avenged Sevenfold','The Stage','17.jpg','AS234235','2016-10-28','The Stage&nbsp;is the seventh&nbsp;studio album&nbsp;by American&nbsp;heavy metal&nbsp;band&nbsp;Avenged Sevenfold. It is a concept album about artificial intelligence and self-destruction of society.[1][2]&nbsp;It was released on October 28, 2016 after a live stream event on the band&#39;s&nbsp;Facebookpage.&nbsp;The Stage&nbsp;is the first Avenged Sevenfold album to feature&nbsp;Brooks Wackerman&nbsp;on drums, after departure of Arin Ilejay in July 2015, and the band&#39;s first album to be released through&nbsp;Capitol Records. It is also the band&#39;s longest studio album at 73 minutes and 35 seconds, thus beating&nbsp;City of Evil&nbsp;by almost a minute. The album also features their longest song to date, &quot;Exist&quot;, with a run-time of 15 minutes and 41 seconds.','<ul>\r\n	<li>The Stage</li>\r\n	<li>Paradigm</li>\r\n	<li>Sunny Disposition</li>\r\n	<li>God Damn</li>\r\n	<li>Creating God</li>\r\n	<li>Angels</li>\r\n	<li>Simulation</li>\r\n	<li>Higher</li>\r\n	<li>Roman Sky</li>\r\n	<li>Fermi Paradox</li>\r\n	<li>Exist</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-stage/id1168724836','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Avenged_Sevenfold_The_Stage?id=Bpeubtn5laq7vw247ck6wsa3bgu','https://play.spotify.com/album/0jwnYwJz6XHNrVAYEclQPd','http://www.deezer.com/album/14411836','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"2\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:2:\"10\";}',17),(18,'Bullet For My Valentine','Don\'t Need You','18.jpg','BFMV49235','2016-11-07','','Don&#39;t Need You','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/dont-need-you-single/id1169683343','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Bullet_For_My_Valentine_Don_t_Need_You?id=Btdi6q46tn6n2tqjurgbidsb7ny','https://play.spotify.com/album/7DRnBLuaOHdetg3zKcrcn0','http://www.deezer.com/album/14476800','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"6\";i:1;s:2:\"10\";i:2;s:2:\"17\";}',18),(19,'Trivium','Ember to Inferno: Ab Initio','19.jpg','TR82423','2016-12-02','The Trivium&nbsp;Ember To Inferno: Ab Initio&nbsp;- Deluxe CD &nbsp;here contains the original Ember to Inferno album with new artwork, plus 13 bonus tracks and an expanded booklet in a digipak. The 13 bonus tracks are the band&#39;s early demos &quot;Ruber&quot; (aka the Red Demo), &quot;Caeruleus&quot; (aka the Blue Demo) and &quot;Flavus&quot; (aka the Yellow Demo).&nbsp;','<ul>\r\n	<li>Inception: The Bleeding Skies</li>\r\n	<li>Pillars of Serpents</li>\r\n	<li>If I Could Collapse the Masses</li>\r\n	<li>Fugue (A Revelation)</li>\r\n	<li>Requiem</li>\r\n	<li>Ember to Inferno</li>\r\n	<li>Ashes</li>\r\n	<li>To Burn the Eye</li>\r\n	<li>Falling to Grey</li>\r\n	<li>My Hatred</li>\r\n	<li>When All Light Dies</li>\r\n	<li>A View of Burning Empires</li>\r\n	<li>Pain (Ruber)</li>\r\n	<li>Thrust (Ruber)</li>\r\n	<li>Lake of Fire (Ruber)</li>\r\n	<li>To Burn the Eye (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>Requiem (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>Fugue (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>My Hatred (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>The Storm (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>Sworn (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>Demon (Caeruleus)</li>\r\n	<li>Like Light to the Flies (Flavus)</li>\r\n	<li>Blinding Tears Will Break the Skies (Flavus)</li>\r\n	<li>The Deceived (Flavus)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ua/album/ember-to-inferno-ab-initio/id1163332639?app=itunes&ign-mpt=uo%3D4','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Trivium_Ember_to_Inferno_Ab_Initio?id=Bvvojumkkzx5ogzynjyat77o3qa&PCamRefID=LFV_cd6beab56baab7a0cd11d9b19df8809b','https://play.spotify.com/album/32AF2NT4Utp4EcG2vaQDIJ','http://www.deezer.com/album/14245186','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"5\";i:1;s:1:\"6\";i:2;s:2:\"10\";}',21),(20,'Animals As Leaders','The Madness Of Many','20.jpg','AAS87636','2016-11-11','The Madness of Many&nbsp;is the fourth album by&nbsp;Animals as Leaders, released in November 2016','<ul>\r\n	<li>Arithmophobia</li>\r\n	<li>Ectogenesis</li>\r\n	<li>Cognitive Contortions</li>\r\n	<li>Inner Assassins</li>\r\n	<li>Private Visions of the World</li>\r\n	<li>Backpfeifengesicht</li>\r\n	<li>Transcentience</li>\r\n	<li>The Glass Bridge</li>\r\n	<li>The Brain Dance</li>\r\n	<li>Apeirophobia</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/the-madness-of-many/id1156714366','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/Animals_As_Leaders_The_Madness_Of_Many?id=Breoab6loksism6bpb2gnhl5tiy','https://play.spotify.com/album/13jTvLPx2N9JbLOmq4yYQW','http://www.deezer.com/album/14520214','a:3:{i:0;s:1:\"4\";i:1;s:1:\"8\";i:2;s:2:\"14\";}',19),(21,'August Burns Red','What Child Is This? (Greensleeves)','21.jpg','ABR89551','2016-11-18',NULL,'<ul>\r\n	<li>What Child Is This? (Greensleeves)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','https://itunes.apple.com/ua/album/what-child-is-this-greensleeves/id1172590211?i=1172590555&app=itunes&ign-mpt=uo%3D4','https://play.google.com/store/music/album/August_Burns_Red_What_Child_Is_This_Greensleeves?id=B5jzg5hjv54nz5pwxivzck23ixa','https:/